modules.description: Processes cron schedule expressions to determine next execution times. Accepts string representations of cron fields and returns parsed time intervals. Used to validate and compute future timestamps for scheduled tasks in system automation workflows.

The module provides functions for parsing, validating, and manipulating crontab entries and schedules, operating on structured data representing time fields like minutes, hours, days, and months, as well as user-specific task tables. It supports converting between POSIX-compliant string formats and structured representations while enabling management operations such as inserting, removing, and inspecting scheduled tasks. These capabilities are essential for automating system workflows, managing user job schedules, and ensuring compliance with time-based execution constraints.
